<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,259,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Note.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Lelej &amp; Kabakov" authorityYear="1980" box="[422,566,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Smicromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atrithorax">
<emphasis box="[422,566,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">S. atrithorax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Skorikov" authorityYear="1935" box="[788,894,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Smicromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kurdus">
<emphasis box="[788,894,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">S. kurdus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected in the same area in 
<collectingCountry box="[1306,1433,259,285]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
. Furthermore, in 
<collectingCountry box="[335,458,295,321]" name="Azerbaijan" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">Azerbaijan</collectingCountry>
the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Morawitz" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[509,615,295,320]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Smicromyrme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turanicus">
<emphasis box="[509,615,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="76">turanicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group is represented by one species known from males and one species known from females; we here treat them as opposite sexes of the same species.
</paragraph>
